  "text": "Julious and Whitehead (2011) gave graphical methods for identifying outliers, and Mavridis et al (2017) gave a stepwise procedure in which studies are progressively added. [CITATION_1] proposed new measures of heterogeneity based on medians that are robust against outliers. Despite all this research, there is as yet no fully 'automatic' way of dealing with outliers, that does not make modelling assumptions about them or require judgement, and this work tries to fill that gap.",
